ce it's the external auditory canal, maybe an infection there.","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.056145,0.10467,0.1195,0.1181,0.10448,0.090252,0.082842,0.074625,0.070464,0.068781,0.056,0.054136],"unified_progress":[0.053651,0.079126,0.092374,0.10755,0.10245,0.096498,0.094802,0.088408,0.084643,0.080362,0.065439,0.054701]},{"section":8,"text":"The granulation tissue suggests chronicity or an ongoing process.","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.045592,0.092923,0.10736,0.10962,0.10285,0.095214,0.09002,0.082605,0.079003,0.074805,0.062862,0.057143],"unified_progress":[0.043206,0.074605,0.089251,0.10291,0.10184,0.098039,0.097158,0.092331,0.089371,0.083654,0.069877,0.057757]},{"section":9,"text":"The presence of pus points to an acute infection.","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.043872,0.089575,0.10613,0.10844,0.10154,0.092321,0.088756,0.082423,0.077932,0.079948,0.066585,0.062472],"unified_progress":[0.042844,0.071521,0.084315,0.095518,0.097243,0.095075,0.096801,0.093625,0.091052,0.091277,0.077674,0.063053]},{"section":10,"text":"Wait, the external auditory canal infection is called otitis externa.","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.04337,0.08292,0.094295,0.099809,0.099507,0.09614,0.093298,0.087776,0.084032,0.080592,0.070412,0.067848],"unified_progress":[0.048079,0.067934,0.082741,0.094791,0.096541,0.09917,0.09682,0.093845,0.090933,0.085983,0.075699,0.067465]},{"section":11,"text":"But with granulation tissue, maybe it's more chronic.","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.042248,0.082649,0.095462,0.10003,0.09854,0.094499,0.092867,0.088784,0.085754,0.083664,0.071594,0.063909],"unified_progress":[0.046243,0.070988,0.085456,0.097313,0.099168,0.097526,0.097744,0.094805,0.091608,0.08767,0.073077,0.058402]},{"section":12,"text":"But the patient has pus and fever, which are acute signs.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.035437,0.073801,0.086117,0.091786,0.094665,0.095318,0.09729,0.095344,0.091597,0.089624,0.081546,0.067475],"unified_progress":[0.06052,0.068826,0.077245,0.084317,0.0908,0.092396,0.094854,0.09689,0.094034,0.095151,0.081941,0.063025]},{"section":13,"text":"However, uncontrolled diabetes can lead to more severe or atypical infections.","dimension":9,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.034956,0.069726,0.080542,0.088523,0.094789,0.099807,0.099402,0.097594,0.093045,0.091173,0.081558,0.068885],"unified_progress":[0.062552,0.082495,0.081764,0.082796,0.086655,0.091414,0.091265,0.094254,0.090617,0.090031,0.081195,0.064962]},{"section":14,"text":"Otitis externa is usually caused by bacteria like Pseudomonas or Staph, especially in diabetics.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.031362,0.067575,0.082681,0.094103,0.10064,0.10252,0.10259,0.096633,0.089267,0.08997,0.075006,0.067656],"unified_progress":[0.040492,0.067352,0.088212,0.092411,0.096804,0.10298,0.10075,0.097656,0.092167,0.087819,0.073794,0.059561]},{"section":15,"text":"The granulation tissue might be from chronic otitis externa, but the acute symptoms suggest an exacerbation.","dimension":9,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.02915,0.064593,0.078607,0.088587,0.095148,0.098752,0.10172,0.098092,0.096276,0.090777,0.083359,0.074937],"unified_progress":[0.041977,0.057831,0.071996,0.08246,0.090424,0.098679,0.097204,0.098181,0.099548,0.096351,0.090115,0.075234]},{"section":16,"text":"Alternatively, could it be malignant otitis externa?","dimension":0,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.028074,0.063004,0.077884,0.088058,0.095948,0.098892,0.10159,0.10143,0.099286,0.094874,0.083903,0.067056],"unified_progress":[0.034191,0.065506,0.084184,0.097231,0.099467,0.10082,0.10243,0.099067,0.095696,0.09001,0.074811,0.056585]},{"section":17,"text":"That's a severe infection, usually in diabetics, caused by Pseudomonas, leading to necrotizing external otitis.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.027239,0.061183,0.076217,0.090109,0.10023,0.10488,0.10657,0.10136,0.093607,0.092181,0.077548,0.068874],"unified_progress":[0.034246,0.059296,0.078078,0.089617,0.096914,0.10856,0.10472,0.10237,0.097501,0.090826,0.07655,0.061319]},{"section":18,"text":"It can destroy bone and cause granulation tissue, along with fever and severe pain.","dimension":9,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.027393,0.061547,0.074101,0.084841,0.093871,0.10006,0.10434,0.10177,0.098799,0.094062,0.08539,0.073818],"unified_progress":[0.035838,0.056041,0.070348,0.080773,0.090276,0.10089,0.099792,0.10167,0.10236,0.10021,0.090265,0.071533]},{"section":19,"text":"Malignant otitis externa is a possibility here.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.028944,0.060891,0.074317,0.085195,0.092877,0.096297,0.099099,0.096911,0.094099,0.094721,0.08572,0.090928],"unified_progress":[0.03329,0.053342,0.070073,0.081181,0.087196,0.096333,0.097271,0.099387,0.098521,0.096525,0.094004,0.092878]},{"section":20,"text":"The patient's uncontrolled diabetes makes them more susceptible.","dimension":11,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.0332,0.067958,0.078424,0.085747,0.093023,0.10222,0.098987,0.098719,0.094958,0.093351,0.083603,0.069813],"unified_progress":[0.089592,0.10836,0.090921,0.08317,0.08293,0.084436,0.081558,0.086998,0.081237,0.077618,0.072047,0.061131]},{"section":21,"text":"The granulation tissue in the canal, along with the fever and purulent discharge, fits.","dimension":4,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.030315,0.064986,0.075586,0.082722,0.08834,0.093287,0.096819,0.096066,0.10327,0.094336,0.092132,0.082141],"unified_progress":[0.046081,0.07218,0.082616,0.088189,0.0945,0.095159,0.094489,0.093194,0.097611,0.088468,0.080587,0.066927]},{"section":22,"text":"The term \"malignant\" refers to its aggressive nature, not cancer.","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.037761,0.069251,0.078039,0.085125,0.08975,0.091555,0.094029,0.093317,0.09143,0.093198,0.086105,0.090439],"unified_progress":[0.050209,0.06114,0.073362,0.081847,0.086723,0.093237,0.093363,0.095033,0.093964,0.093933,0.090672,0.086517]},{"section":23,"text":"Another thought: could it be just acute otitis externa?","dimension":0,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.026963,0.059217,0.075027,0.084483,0.093134,0.095495,0.099347,0.10189,0.10083,0.099253,0.090563,0.073803],"unified_progress":[0.034022,0.065918,0.083144,0.09485,0.096778,0.096888,0.10032,0.09887,0.096007,0.092314,0.07928,0.06161]},{"section":24,"text":"But the granulation tissue might indicate chronic changes.","dimension":6,"group":2,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.02492,0.057541,0.072405,0.083135,0.091781,0.096941,0.10255,0.10246,0.1029,0.09717,0.092106,0.076094],"unified_progress":[0.08247,0.06539,0.075176,0.083589,0.090338,0.092306,0.09327,0.095019,0.092028,0.088838,0.078173,0.063404]},{"section":25,"text":"However, the acute symptoms and fever might point to an acute exacerbation.","dimension":9,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.024375,0.054347,0.067935,0.079006,0.088869,0.095478,0.10209,0.10302,0.10277,0.10009,0.096266,0.085752],"unified_progress":[0.053413,0.057654,0.067969,0.076799,0.08505,0.090781,0.093845,0.097786,0.099068,0.10058,0.095258,0.081794]},{"section":26,"text":"But in diabetics, especially uncontrolled, malignant otitis externa is a more serious consideration.","dimension":11,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.027882,0.057066,0.068587,0.07813,0.086737,0.093836,0.097258,0.098821,0.098698,0.099204,0.094998,0.098784],"unified_progress":[0.05021,0.068948,0.071228,0.074545,0.078527,0.085798,0.087124,0.093072,0.094089,0.095532,0.099092,0.10184]},{"section":27,"text":"Malignant otitis externa often starts with pain and drainage, then progresses to more severe symptoms like granulation, bone erosion (like temporal bone), and systemic signs like fever.","dimension":9,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.026733,0.059063,0.071122,0.082223,0.091562,0.098205,0.10296,0.10113,0.10029,0.096614,0.089497,0.080611],"unified_progress":[0.034087,0.055477,0.072536,0.080201,0.089292,0.097806,0.098451,0.10064,0.10275,0.10039,0.092219,0.07616]},{"section":28,"text":"The patient's age and diabetes are risk factors.","dimension":11,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.027314,0.060303,0.073779,0.083093,0.091817,0.10056,0.10059,0.10117,0.099358,0.097937,0.090019,0.074061],"unified_progress":[0.089422,0.095603,0.084211,0.081174,0.083535,0.086007,0.085553,0.089187,0.085178,0.083573,0.075378,0.06118]},{"section":29,"text":"So putting it all together, the most likely diagnosis is malignant otitis externa.","dimension":7,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.025142,0.047243,0.056303,0.064045,0.071324,0.077419,0.08467,0.088852,0.096383,0.10137,0.11408,0.17317],"unified_progress":[0.032248,0.040521,0.049803,0.058987,0.063061,0.07173,0.078,0.084325,0.094766,0.10446,0.1398,0.1823]},{"section":30,"text":"The key clues are the uncontrolled diabetes, granulation tissue, pus, fever, and severe pain.","dimension":4,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.017128,0.039316,0.051958,0.062103,0.074154,0.084509,0.093506,0.1002,0.11072,0.11717,0.1276,0.12164],"unified_progress":[0.024945,0.039563,0.050962,0.060412,0.072767,0.088695,0.092161,0.10252,0.11448,0.1244,0.12585,0.10323]},{"section":31,"text":"Regular otitis externa wouldn't typically present with systemic symptoms like fever and such severe tissue changes unless it's the malignant form.","dimension":9,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.021983,0.049507,0.060818,0.071204,0.081258,0.090326,0.099004,0.10319,0.10609,0.10789,0.10688,0.10185],"unified_progress":[0.026532,0.043993,0.056006,0.065732,0.077694,0.088625,0.095228,0.1044,0.11072,0.11712,0.1153,0.098653]}]}}